# Rocket.new — Developer Quick Reference

> ⚠️ CRITICAL RULES AT THE VERY TOP AND REPEATED AT THE BOTTOM.
> These are the patterns that cause the most bugs in Rocket projects.

---

## 🚨 THE 7 RULES THAT CAUSE 90% OF BUGS

```typescript
// ❌→✅  1. SERVER CODE: getUser() not getSession()
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()  // ✅
const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession()  // ❌ server-side

// ❌→✅  2. STRIPE WEBHOOKS: request.text() not request.json()
const body = await request.text()   // ✅ raw — required for signature
const body = await request.json()   // ❌ destroys raw bytes

// ❌→✅  3. SERVER COMPONENTS: use server client, not browser client
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'  // ✅
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/client'  // ❌ in Server Component

// ❌→✅  4. MIDDLEWARE LOCATION: root level, not inside /app
// middleware.ts   ✅   |   app/middleware.ts  ❌

// ❌→✅  5. NEXT.JS 15: await cookies()
const cookieStore = await cookies()  // ✅
const cookieStore = cookies()        // ❌ breaks in Next.js 15

// ❌→✅  6. SERVICE ROLE KEY: server only, never NEXT_PUBLIC_
process.env.SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY         // ✅
process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE  // ❌ exposed to browser

// ❌→✅  7. SUPABASE PACKAGE: @supabase/ssr, not deprecated auth-helpers
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr'  // ✅
import { createServerComponentClient } from '@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs'  // ❌
```

