## 🩺 FIRST 5 DIAGNOSTIC COMMANDS (Run on Any Broken Project)

```bash
# 1. TypeScript errors — catches 60% of build failures
npx tsc --noEmit

# 2. Find getSession() in server code (broken auth)
grep -rn "getSession()" ./app ./lib ./middleware.ts

# 3. Verify env vars load
node -e "require('dotenv').config({path:'.env.local'}); console.log('URL:', !!process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL)"

# 4. Find deprecated Supabase package usage
grep -rn "auth-helpers-nextjs" ./app ./lib ./package.json

# 5. Clear Next.js cache (fixes ~20% of weird issues)
rm -rf .next && npm run dev
```

